      "value": "Kimi Delta Attention and Attention Residuals with Stable LatentMoE; 16 of 896 experts activate per token."
    },
    {
      "name": "context_caching",
      "value": "Automatic for regular requests; no cache ID, TTL, or extra parameter is required."
    },
    {
      "name": "benchmark_methodology",
      "value": "Moonshot's release-table Kimi K3 results use max reasoning effort, temperature 1.0, and top_p 1.0. Agent harnesses vary by benchmark; each score records its harness and other material conditions."
    },
    {
      "name": "benchmark_multimodal_runs",
      "value": "All multimodal results except ZeroBench are averaged over three runs. ZeroBench follows the official pass@5 setting and is run five times."
    },
    {
      "name": "benchmark_thinking_history_note",
      "value": "K3 requires the complete preserved thinking history to be passed back between turns. Moonshot warns that incompatible harnesses or switching models mid-session can make evaluation quality unstable."
    },
    {
      "name": "benchmark_source_date",
      "value": "2026-07-16T00:00:00Z"
    },
    {
      "name": "availability_note",
      "value": "Moonshot AI and Venice provide Kimi K3 API access. Venice currently exposes the standard kimi-k3 route; its live model catalog does not yet expose an E2EE Kimi K3 model ID. Moonshot says full model weights will be released by July 27, 2026, with further architecture, training, and evaluation details in the technical report."
    }
